Philippine share prices closed 0.15 percent lower on Tuesday, weighed down by the downturn in foreign markets, dealers said. The composite index closed 1.60 points lower to 1,038.07, while the all-share index lost 15.11 points to 634.98. Losers outnumbered gainers 27 to 13 while 33 stocks were unchanged. Turnover reached 267.67 million shares worth 113.09 million pesos (2.11 million US dollars) against Monday's 190.14 million shares worth 179.24 million pesos (3.34 million dollars). Enditem 